		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Furigana</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Furigana</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja"><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E6%8C%AF%E3%82%8A%E4%BB%AE%E5%90%8D" class="extiw" title="wikt:振り仮名">振り仮名</a></span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> is a <a href="/wiki/Japanese_language" title="Japanese language">Japanese</a> reading aid, consisting of smaller <a href="/wiki/Kana" title="Kana">kana</a> printed next to a <a href="/wiki/Kanji" title="Kanji">kanji</a> or other character to indicate its <a href="/wiki/Pronunciation" title="Pronunciation">pronunciation</a>. In horizontal text, <i><a href="/wiki/Yokogaki_and_tategaki" title="Yokogaki and tategaki" class="mw-redirect">yokogaki</a></i>, they are placed above the line of text, while in vertical text, <i><a href="/wiki/Yokogaki_and_tategaki" title="Yokogaki and tategaki" class="mw-redirect">tategaki</a></i>, they are placed to the right of the line of text, as illustrated below. They are one type of <a href="/wiki/Ruby_character" title="Ruby character">ruby</a> text. <i>Furigana</i> are also known as <b>yomigana</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja"><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E8%AA%AD%E3%81%BF%E4%BB%AE%E5%90%8D" class="extiw" title="wikt:読み仮名">読み仮名</a></span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> or <b>rubi</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja"><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E3%83%AB%E3%83%93" class="extiw" title="wikt:ルビ">ルビ</a></span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> in Japanese.</p>
